courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon completion of the course, students would be able to:

1) Identify key recent archaeological discoveries of China;
2) Analyze the functions and meanings of archaeological finds in particular contexts;
3) Acquire research techniques in reading primary data; and

4) Think critically about archaeological presentations, such as museum exhibitions, and relevant cultural events

- Learn the basic mode of governance and operation of cultural institutions and understand their impacts in shaping the practice of cultural management;
- Acquire the basic knowledge and technique in implementing cultural programmes;
- Understand the dynamic among governmental infrastructure, community and cultural institutions;
- Build a solid foundation for further and more specialized studies in cultural management.
